Today, I chaired a meeting of the Council of Ministers at the Presidential Palace in Abu Dhabi, during which we decided to launch the National Program for Tolerance in the UAE. Https://t.co/iIgCK14gQ1

The Minister of Tolerance presented us with the most important axes of the program, which is based on our religion, our Constitution, our history, our values ​​and the international charters we have committed to.

The Government will launch a Center for Tolerance Studies and a Charter for Tolerance and Coexistence. We will establish the value of tolerance in our society through programs and campaigns and protect them through legislation.
We will also have a program of tolerance responsibility for institutions to discard any kind of discrimination in government or private institutions based on race, color or religion
Our goal is to protect our society from the winds of intolerance and hatred that afflict many societies around us and to establish a model that can benefit our region
Today, we adopted an anti-dumping law to limit the impact of subsidized imports from their countries and to ensure a minimum level of fair competition with our national products

We have adopted the executive regulations of the Small and Medium Enterprises Law with a view to unifying legislation, mechanisms, facilities and incentives for the citizens of the owners of these projects
